    "'coming to believe P') bring about movements that they rationalise as actions.",
    "These events are the links in the chains, the steps on the pathways, that ultimately make up the picture of reality that both rationalising and ordinary causal explanation fit into.",
    "According to this picture, event causation is the \"cement of the universe\" (Davidson, 2001a, p. xv), 7 binding events, whether described in the language of physics or psychology, into a single nexus of intersecting causal pathways.",
    "8 A causal story about how the agent fulfilled her goal traces a series of events backwards along one such causal pathway, and this maps onto the means-end structure represented by the belief-desire pair at that same pathway's beginning.",
    "As a description of the psychology of intentional action, this basic model is, of course, too basic."
